basicQuestions.answerText:
The cause of simple cryoglobulinemia is unknown. It occurs mainly in people with cancers of the immune system, such as <a href="https://medlineplus.gov/multiplemyeloma.html" target="_blank">multiple myeloma</a> and <a href="https://medlineplus.gov/lymphoma.html" target="_blank">non-Hodgkin's lymphoma</a>.[15671] <br />
<br />
In some cases, cryoglobulinemia occurs in someone with no underlying health condition. In these cases, it is known as essential or idiopathic cryoglobulinemia.[15668]&nbsp;&nbsp;
